author: from staff reports
title: Fing, Potomac State blank Allegany, 5-0
text:
Fing, Potomac State blank Allegany, 5-0 from staff reports The Cumberland Times-News 
CUMBERLAND — Rhys Fing scored a pair of goals in the first half and the Potomac State Catamounts got out to a 4-0 lead by intermission during a 5-0 shutout of Allegany College Thursday afternoon in junior college action. 
Mountain Ridge graduate Tyler Sisler recorded the first goal less than 10 minutes into play on an unassisted goal, before Fing scored back-to-back at 11:15 and 17:42. Leo Sanchez assisted on the first goal and Sisler got the assist on the second. 
Sisler then assisted Aaron Osei with 31:46 for the fourth and final goal of the half. 
Jacob Williams scored 5:46 into the second half to make it 5-0. 
The Cats split time between two goalies with Kevin Riley making three saves and Alec Sproule stopping two shots. ACM’s Mitch Winters finished with two saves. Potomac State outshot Allegany 13-5 and led 11-3 in corner kicks.
